OL,3,CHow can you avoid falling victim to a
OL,4,Cphone or online scam?
OL,6,FThe study revealed that 23% of older
OL,7,Fpeople surveyed - 2,000 in total -
OL,8,Fhave confronted scammers over the
OL,9,Fphone.
OL,11,FMore than a quarter of people over 65
OL,12,F(28%) receive multiple scam calls,
OL,13,Ftexts, or emails each week, while
OL,14,Fthose aged 55 to 64 face the highest
OL,15,Fnumber of scams.
OL,17,FITV News spoke to pensioner Kate Hall
OL,18,Fabout how she confronted a fake scam
OL,19,Fcomputer help desk and never backed
OL,20,Fdown.
