OL,3,CHow can you avoid falling victim to a
OL,4,Cphone or online scam?
OL,6,FDespite the increased confidence of
OL,7,Folder people to confront scammers, the
OL,8,Fstudy shows almost a third of people
OL,9,Faged over 65 (27%) are not confident
OL,10,Fin their digital skills.
OL,12,FAmy Caton, a senior project manager at
OL,13,FBT Group, advised pensioners to
OL,14,Fcontinue to build their digital skills
OL,15,Fand ability to stay safe online.
OL,17,FShe told ITV News: "(Older people)
OL,18,Fdon't be scared by these experiences,
OL,19,Fuse it to fuel your learning."
